lines.text: BACK TO BASICS: FOOD AND SHELTER FOR THE ELDERLY
Twenty-Seventh Annual Southern Conference on Gerontology
The basic life styles of the elderly, reflected in their needs for and patterns of housing and food consumption.
continue to be important subjects for research and serious consideration in community service planning. All
types of service delivery are inextricably bound to the basic issues of the differential availability and
consumption of food and shelter. The 27th Annual Conference will selectively approach the full range of issues
in these areas. with an eye to integrating this information to improve basic understanding and to promote
